A map of Puro-Puro: Blue = portal, Yellow = wheat, Red = where the wheat withers away.

On a good day, hunting down implings can yield quite a bit of money for willing players. The elusive Dragon impling at Impetuous Impulses or throughout Gielinor is exceedingly rare, but it is valuable and worth 473,181.

Players can reach Puro-Puro by travelling to Lumbridge Swamp and entering the Lost City shed with a Dramen or Lunar staff equipped. Alternatively, they can use a Fairy ring if sufficient progress in Fairytale II - Cure a Queen has been made. Unlike the permanent crop circle in Zanaris, there are other crop circles that periodically spawn in wheat fields throughout Gielinor.

After entering the crop circle to access Puro-Puro, players could begin in the south-east or north-west corner and work the maze. Moreover, players are advised to always save nine jars so they can trade them for an inventory full of jars; otherwise, stock up on low-level implings and exchange them for a jar generator from Elnock Inquisitor.

Around 1-4 dragon implings could be caught on a good hour, which could set the profit margin between 473,181 and 1,892,724. Most likely, however, players will be fortunate enough to catch at least one an hour, so it is advised that they also catch nature, magpie and ninja implings while hunting for dragon imps in order to sustain profitability. Nonetheless, this money-making method has potential to be a very decent money maker.

Due to constantly changing prices on the Grand Exchange, some information in this article may or may not be current.
It is strongly recommended to check the live prices on the Grand Exchange before making large investments in any method.
